result.execSummary:
The defendant Ernesto Lee Rodriguez was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Criminal Damage to Property [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.01(1).
  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief

Defendant Ernesto Lee Rodriguez in court with attorney Michael L. Chernin.  Defendant Ernesto Lee Rodriguez in custody.  Michelle A. Grasso appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: SD.
Sentencing proceeded.

AS TO COUNT 3:  The Court sentenced the defendant to serve 9 MONTHS in the House of Correction, consecutive to case 22CM451 and Count 4, with credit for 0 days time served.  

AS TO COUNT 4:  The Court sentenced the defendant to serve 166 DAYS in the House of Correction, consecutive to case 22CM451 and Count 3, with credit for 166 days.  THIS IS A TIME SERVED DISPOSITION.

AS TO COUNT 3:  The court STAYED the sentence and placed the defendant on probation for a period of 2 YEARS with the following conditions:

- Alcohol and drug assessment and comply with any treatment deemed necessary by the department.
- Absolute sobriety with random urine screens and breathalyzer.
- Complete a batter's intervention program.
- Complete a parenting class.
- No contact with OCT.
- Court set restitution at $0.
- Court ordered Defendant to provide a DNA sample and pay applicable surcharge. 
- Court ordered Defendant to pay all costs, fees, and surcharges (including DNA and DV) during the period of Probation. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment. 

*Court DENIES expungement.

Defendant Ernesto Lee Rodriguez in court with attorney Michael L. Chernin.  Defendant Ernesto Lee Rodriguez in custody.  Michelle A. Grasso appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: SD.  
Defendant prepared to enter change of plea.  Hearing proceeded.  Negotiations set forth by the state.

AS TO COUNTS 3 AND 4: Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record. Defendant shall provide a DNA sample for the Data Bank. 

AS TO COUNTS 1 AND 2: Pursuant to plea negotiations and on State's motion, Court orders charge dismissed but read-in for sentencing purposes.

Court advised defendant due to this DV conviction he may never possess firearms or ammunition.
